ing, and driving business growth, operating based on turnover and profit percentage systems.  Managed project planning and site progress planning at M/S Experio Tech Pvt. Ltd., a manufacturer and integrator of high-end security gadgets for traffic enforcement and surveillance. Products cater to Police, Traffic Police, Transport Department, Indian Army, and Air Force.  Planned production control activities to optimize runtime, ensuring high quality, timely delivery, and cost-effectiveness.  Finalized costing with suppliers for new developments and achieved cost reductions in existing products while maintaining high quality standards.  Overall responsible for procurement of consumables, child parts, and key equipment from domestic sources as well as imports from USA, Hong Kong, Germany, UK, and other countries.  Monitored logistics agencies and managed their cost aspects to ensure efficient and costeffective transportation and delivery  Ensured delivery commitments by conducting daily analyses of reports from all relevant departments.  Provided day-to-day troubleshooting for issues across all departments, addressing concerns of employees and suppliers. || Senior Manager - PPC & Sales | Maxop Engineering Co. Pvt. Ltd | 2014-2015 |  Developed and implemented production plans based on sales orders and pending orders to ensure efficient manufacturing and timely delivery.  Managed planning, procurement, and dispatch scheduling for over 4,000 automotive underchassis components, ensuring efficient supply chain operations.  Ensured quality product delivery by managing overall production planning operations, including coordination with marketing, manpower management, supply chain logistics, and equipment uptime.  Ensured timely achievement of production targets while adhering to cost parameters  Monitored tool maintenance and ensured their readiness according to the production plan.  Assisted in developing plans for new tools based on forecasts and existing production schedules.  Monitored raw materials, work in progress, and finished goods across various functional departments. CHANDER JEET YADAV cj1973yadav@gmail.com Page 5 of 7  Participated in the systematic implementation of quality initiatives such as 5S, Kaizen, QRAP, and QRQC, aiming for zero breakdowns, zero accidents, and zero customer complaints.  Led, mentored, and monitored the performance of operators to ensure process efficiency and achievement of production targets.  Created and maintained a dynamic environment that fosters development opportunities and motivates high performance among team members. Monitored and analyzed buffer stocks in the finished goods store to ensure compliance with customer-approved norms and timely order fulfillment. || Manager - Quality (BOC) | HJS Emission Technology India Pvt. Ltd | 2012-2013 | ● Aligned the company''s quality policy with the standards of the parent company, HJS-Menden (Germany). ● Conducted regular meetings and site visits with suppliers to ensure quality and compliance with standards. ● Monitored production processes at the supplier’s facility to ensure adherence to quality and delivery standards. ● Developed and implemented supplier management strategies, including supplier development through error analysis and the creation of remedial, corrective, and preventive actions. ● Upgraded suppliers through process audits and targeted training programs. ● Handled internal and external complaints, implementing preventive actions based on root cause analysis. ● Directed test procedures and methods and verified related documentation for accuracy and compliance. || Manager –PPC | Maxop Engineering Pvt. Ltd., | 2011-2012 | ● Involved in verifying losses across all shops by reconciling data recorded in the ERP system. ● Established coordination between HPDC and various stages of production, including Trimming, Trimming to Finishing, Finishing to WIP Store, WIP Store to Machining Cells (3 shops), and finally Machining to Finished Goods (FG). ● Played a pivotal role in the development of trimming dies for new projects and managed the routine repair and maintenance of existing trimming dies. ● Demonstrated excellence in designing Management Reporting Mechanism (MRM) and Management Information System (MIS) reports for the department. ● Spearheaded the team of 242 members integrated and motivated, comes under my departments. ● Instrumental in key parameters in the specified range like Finishing / Trimming Cost / Part, Sanctioned v/s actual man hours, inventory figures in WIP & FG area, loss hours due to no material and plan failure, transportation cost / part, etc. CHANDER JEET YADAV cj1973yadav@gmail.com Page 6 of 7 || Manager- PPC & Operations | Tungsten India Pvt. Ltd. (Unit of Maxop Engineering Pvt. ltd.) | 2007-2011 |  Ensuring quality product delivery; managing overall operations involved in production planning including coordinating in marketing, manpower management, supplies and up-time of equipments.  Looking after the Planning and Operations of Tungsten Disc Manufacturing and complete production and finishing section of Aluminium Die Casting products.  Cost Analysis, Labor availability, MIS report Preparation, Monitoring Inventory, New Developments for process and latest techniques.  Cost analysis of contractual work, Designed Incentive module and slabs. || Assistant Manager | Spinx Auto Pvt. Ltd. (Unit of Mark Exhaust Systems Pvt. Ltd) | 1999-2006 |  Looked after for customer co-ordination related to technical part of our products.  Preparing the plan for production in accordance with the schedule.  Co-ordination with Quality Assurance for Quality status of bought out Items and Raw Material.  Preparing the road map for shipment / container dispatches. || Trainee Engineer to Senior Engineer | Mark Auto Ind. Ltd. | 1995-1999 |  Joined as Trainee Engineer and reached the position of Production Engineer Holds the distinction of achieving production targets & completed the schedule as per the plan received from Customers for Press Shop & Assembly Shop. Exposure for Automobile Exhaust manufacturing on COMAS (ITALY) machines line.  Training on Low-Cost Automation from Quality Austria Central Asia.  Leadership Skill Training from Quality Austria Central Asia.  Internal Auditor Course for ISO 14001: 2004 (EMS).  Internal Auditor Course ISO/TS 16949: 2009 from Quality Austria central Asia.  Well versed with Windows 7/10/11, MS Office (Excel/Word/PowerPoint), ERP & Networking.  Attended training based on Basic Leadership Mountaineering.  Accredited with Best Rock Climber Award at state level during Refresher Rock Climbing Course in 1990.  Independently lead the Cycle Expedition as Team Leader from Delhi to Dhauj in 1991. Other Details CHANDER JEET YADAV cj1973yadav@gmail.com Page 7 of 7  Father’s Name : Late Sh. Harish Chander Yadav  Date of Birth : 6th December 1973.  Address : Flat No.-29, Meghdoot Apartment, Sector 10-A, Gurgaon – 122001,  Languages Known : English, Hindi, Punjabi, and Haryanvi  Location Preference : Any Part of India. Chander Jeet Yadav Date: - Personal Dossier"}]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[{"title":"Imported accomplishment","description":" Led the Purchase Department for all major, minor, and bulk purchases, including machinery,; equipment, and capital items, as well as equipment hiring; successfully negotiated contracts,; achieved cost savings of 46%, and ensured timely procurement to support project timelines.;  Monitored and analyzed purchase trends and rates, verified cost comparison sheets, and; finalized vendors, testing agencies, and other service providers, leading to a streamlined; procurement process and cost savings of 19%.;  Made significant contributions in the ‘automobile ancillaries’ sector by handling various key; roles, including driving impactful projects and initiatives.;  Involved in verifying losses across all shops by reconciling data recorded in the ERP system,; ensuring accuracy